Subject: [PATCH 19/47] wpa_supplicant: declare 20/40 coex support [UPSTREAM]

Set the appropriate bit in the extended capabilities IE

Signed-off-by: Eliad Peller <eliad@wizery.com>
---
 wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.c b/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.c
index 911d79d..a7307b8 100644
--- a/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.c
+++ b/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.c
@@ -1701,6 +1701,7 @@ static void wpas_ext_capab_byte(struct wpa_supplicant *wpa_s, u8 *pos, int idx)
 
 	switch (idx) {
 	case 0: /* Bits 0-7 */
+		*pos |= 0x01; /* Bit 0 - 20/40 Coex */
 		break;
 	case 1: /* Bits 8-15 */
 		if (wpa_s->conf->coloc_intf_reporting) {
